            ],
            "name": "Diverse Elementals",
            "sources": [
              {
                "errata": {
                  "alt": "1.1",
                  "aonid": 221,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "1.1",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "link": {
                  "alt": "Monster Core pg. 148",
                  "aonid": 221,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "Monster Core pg. 148",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "Monster Core",
                "page": 148,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "The Elemental Planes are more than expanses of sky, rock, metal fire, wood, and ocean. Clouds of fog, dust, and storms float through the Plane of Air. The Plane of Earth includes verdant groves, shining metal and crystal, and irradiated wastelands. The Plane of Fire features magma, suffocating smoke, and radiant firelight. Amid the endless sea of the Plane of Water are pockets of ooze and brine, plus the otherworldly environs of the deep.",
            "type": "section"
          },
          {
            "links": [
              {
                "alt": "icewyrm",
                "aonid": 666,
                "game-obj": "Monsters",
                "name": "icewyrm",
                "type": "link"
              },
              {
                "alt": "firewyrm",
                "aonid": 2983,
                "game-obj": "Monsters",
                "name": "firewyrm",
                "type": "link"
              }
            ],
            "name": "Elemental Wyrms",
            "sources": [
              {
                "errata": {
                  "alt": "1.1",
                  "aonid": 221,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "1.1",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "link": {
                  "alt": "Monster Core pg. 148",
                  "aonid": 221,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "Monster Core pg. 148",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "Monster Core",
                "page": 148,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "The icewyrm is the most widely encountered elemental wyrm, but others exist as well, including the blazing firewyrm, the sleek but somewhat smaller sparkwyrm, and the largest of them all, the immense and acidic sludgewyrm.",
            "type": "section"
          },
          {
            "links": [
              {
                "alt": "persistent fire damage",
                "aonid": 86,
                "game-obj": "Conditions",
                "name": "persistent fire damage",
                "type": "link"
              }
            ],
            "name": "Flame and Fathom Meet",
            "sources": [
              {
                "errata": {
                  "alt": "1.1",
                  "aonid": 221,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "1.1",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "link": {
                  "alt": "Monster Core pg. 148",
                  "aonid": 221,
                  "game-obj": "Sources",
                  "name": "Monster Core pg. 148",
                  "type": "link"
                },
                "name": "Monster Core",
                "page": 148,
                "type": "source"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Though fire and water classically oppose one another, in the right mixture they can become a dangerous combination. Water elementals heated to a scalding temperature through natural factors such as underwater volcanoes might deal 1d6 persistent fire damage with their Strikes, while fire elementals infused with moisture might exude clouds of obscuring or even blinding steam.",
            "type": "section"
          },
          {
            "links": [
              {
                "alt": "Elemental, Air",
                "aonid": 41,
                "game-obj": "MonsterFamilies",
                "name": "Elemental, Air",
                "type": "link"
              },
              {
